Results.ReviewText: I couldn't start my day without my best friend 'Nescafe Gold', I couldn't get through the day without my life line 'Nescafe Gold' I couldn't curl up and enjoy my favourite book, without my comforting 'Nescafe Gold', and I couldn't relax in front of the TV without my delicious 'Nescafe Gold'.......Thank you for always being there when I need you. xx
Results.Title: Nescafe Gold is my BFF

Results.ReviewText: I have gotten drawn in to coffee advertising and tried everything on the market. I know now it's a complete waste of time, they're either tasteless or have a bitter edge. Nescafe it made from beans that are fully ripened hence the full bodied smooth taste. I simply could not operate without Nescafe Gold Blend, why do others try to invent the wheel?
Results.Title: Simply the best

Results.ReviewText: The quality of Nescafe is always good which is the reason for why I almost always get Nescafe; my preferance over its competitors is strong. However, the 4 star rating relates to the taste - I prefer the original rather than the gold blend in taste and overall quality. Price wise, it suits the quality of the product and I will definitely buy again.
Results.Title: Greate taste

Results.ReviewText: Usually buy this when it's on offer but we bought a few jars of local coffee home from our holiday in Spain so we haven't bought this for a while. Used to be fine. Reasonable taste, reasonably smooth and not bitter - which is important to me as I don't have sugar with my coffee but other reviewers seem to think that it has gone down hill recently!
Results.Title: Seems like it used to be good

Results.ReviewText: I brought this and really love the smooth flavour. It is definitely what you need first thing in the morning to wake you up. A smooth dark coffee which has a great flavour. Excellent as a sit down coffee, perfect for coffee on the move and wonderful for arrival at work. The coffee has a layered flavour that delivers perfectly with or without milk.
Results.Title: Fantastic wake up!

Results.ReviewText:
Changed to Gold Blend years ago and never regretted it. I noticed the change in jar design first and didn't  initially know the blend has slightly changed, until I tried it.  The taste is just as good, if not better. The main thing I've noticed the coffee is more consistent in taste. 
It seems to allow for me making silly measurement mistakes.
Results.Title: Best Instant Coffee on the Market

Results.ReviewText: I just love to pour and go and with an aroma that makes you go ahhhhhhhh and actually feel like you've had a real fresh coffee, just as coffee should be. It does what it should. Simple, full bodied flavour and simple on the go. Why pay to get one cup of coffee on the go, when you can have several made just how you like for almost the same price
Results.Title: great taste

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, it's sad to hear you're not a fan of the changes we've made but thanks for getting in touch & letting us know!

Results.ReviewText: My wife bought 6 jars of the new recipe Gold Blend, I have always drunk GB at home and at work we all used it. Since the new receipe has come out I don't like it at all, there is a bitter after taste, I have to use more milk to counter that. Nescafe GB has always had a smooth taste almost like ground coffee. I do not think I will buy any more.
Results.Title: New recipe not as good as previous one.

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for getting in touch & letting us know! It's sad to hear you're not liking the changes but we appreciate your feedback.

Results.ReviewText: Been drinking one jar of gold blend a week for years.the new jar is lovely but it's the contents that counts. The flavour is ruined and the dregs left isn't nice. it also leaves a nasty taste.Please change it back. It's such a disappointment when opening a new jar, you no longer get hit with fresh coffee aroma. Will be looking for a new brand.
Results.Title: Change it back

Results.ReviewText: I usually use Blend 37 or coffee beans. However, while on holiday could get neither so bought a jar of Gold Blend and I'm so glad I did. The taste is sublime, earthy yet subtle, tastes like ground coffee beans but without the sometimes bitter flavour. It dissolves quickly and also makes a delicious iced coffee. Well done Nescafe I'm a convert!
Results.Title: Gorgeous taste

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe Gold Blend is my favourite coffee. In my office there is a brew fund where everyone chips in. The problem is that they buy a different well known brand of coffee. Nescafe Gold Blemd is far nicer in my opinion. I keep it locked in my draw. Some of my colleagues also prefer Nescafe Gold Blend, so are always asking me for a spoon of it!.
Results.Title: My special work coffee

Results.ReviewText: to be honest i do prefer the old nescafe gold blend , found that with the new one when u get to the bottom of your coffee it tends to have a dark brown lookin on your coffee .which i find of puttin so i tend to shop about for the old style coffee in nescafe gold blend ,i still purchase it as i do like the coffee but not the new as much thanxs
Results.Title: nescafe gold blend

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe Gold Blend coffee has been my favorite cuppa  for years until the recent new jar shape change. Although the aroma is still enticing, it is not as tasty as previously supplied.   Also I am finding the price has gone up quite steeply in most shops. This stated, I will still purchase this coffee as it is better than most other brands.
Results.Title: Drink coffee

Results.ReviewText: I bought this coffee and I'm really pleased with it, its got a very nice blend although friends have found it to be weak I've personally enjoyed it being weaker, the caffeine isn't as strong then, I let my children 18 and 24 have it, I don't usually allow them because it's too strong but because its much weaker makes it suitable for them.
Results.Title: Pefect for teens and parents!

Results.ReviewText:
I have just brought one of your new Gold Blend and I must say that I do not like the new taste.It is very strong and has a burnt taste.
I used to enjoy my morning coffee but now cannot wait to finish the jar and buy possibly another brand.
I have used your coffee for years and I am disappointed that I will now have to find another brand
Results.Title: Stronger taste

Results.ReviewText: I love my coffee and Gold Blend is always my first choice.  It can sometimes be a tad more pricier than other makes but I watch out for it being on offer and then stock up! I would like to try the other variants of Gold Blend so Nescafe this is for you....how about some samples of these others perhaps in a free sachet attached to the jar?
Results.Title: Mmm

ClientResponses.Response: It's a shame you don't enjoy the changes we've made. Your feedback is very valuable to us and will be shared with the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: I'm a regular Gold Blend drinker and assumed I'd bought the wrong coffee as it was muddy tasting and sludgy so I've bought a new refill only to discover the recipe has changed. I loathe fancy coffees and never frequent American style coffee shops and certainly won't continue to buy Gold Blend now. I hope I can find a suitable replacement.
Results.Title: cheap taste

Results.ReviewText: I bought this 3 weeks ago for my parent and toddler group, the mums are quite fussy about their coffee and this went down a storm, 6 Mum’s complimented the smooth and silky taste 2 of the Mum’s have since purchased a jar. As a busy parent, that 1 cup of delicious coffee may be the only hot drink in a day so quality and taste is paramount!
Results.Title: Does what it says on the jar

Results.ReviewText: Definitely my new favourite - can't wait to get up in the morning to drink it!
Results.Title: My favourite!

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe. We really appreciate your feedback! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText:
We have been drinking Nescafe Gold for years and mistakenly thought that we would like the new version.

It is much weaker than the previous version, leaves a nasty taste in the mouth and powdery dregs in the bottom of the mug.

Please go back to the old recipe as we now have to find an instant coffee from another brand that we like.
Results.Title: Horrible stuff

Results.ReviewText: I bought this before my existing jar ran out, seeing your competition deadline, I opened it 2 days ago to try. I was surprised to find a slight sediment at the bottom of the cup. I expect that is why the taste was better. the sediment wasn't any detriment to the experience. I tried it again today and confirmed my first great impressions.
Results.Title: Outstanding ,yet delicate taste.

Results.ReviewText: We have all walked past that coffee shop on a cold winters day and smelt the aroma escaping into the air, well after buy a jar of gold blend , I took it home opened the lid, pealed back the foil cover and woooooo that coffee aroma hit me. I could not wait to make a cup and drink it and I was not disappointed what a great tatsing coffee.
Results.Title: The great coffee smell

Results.ReviewText: I bought this to try a couple of weeks ago and i loved it. The flavour was so smooth and velvety. I normally use a different brand but i found Gold Blend just had that little bit extra smoothness to it and not at all bitter. Great coffee for giving you energy and warming you up. Good price too. Give it a try as you wont be disappointed.
Results.Title: Great Tasty Coffee

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking gold blend since it was launched,   I thought when the new jar came out the contents would change, as a lot of products do, i was surprised that the taste is better, i think a little stronger but subtly so, the rich flavor and great taste are much are more defined, all in all a great product, keep up the good work.
Results.Title: Is this new gold blend better.

Results.ReviewText: Out of all the Nescafe products, this is the one I prefer. I used to use just the ordinary Nescafe, but sometimes found it a bit on the strong side, even when using just a small amount, always had to add more milk. Started using the Gold Blend and find it just right, smooth, creamy, just what I need to help me wake up for night shift.
Results.Title: Wakey Wakey, rise and shine

Results.ReviewText: Bought this as I always buy Nescafe Gold Blend. Like the new design labelling but overall I don't think the taste has really changed but then I'm no connoisseur.  It still tastes terrific and is still sold as refillable which is very important. I buy the coffee for everyone in the household to drink and have never had a complaint yet!
Results.Title: Lovely smooth taste

ClientResponses.Response: Thank you very much for taking the time & leaving your thoughts on the new recipe. It's disappointing to hear you're not a fan of the changes but we really appreciate you letting us know!

Results.ReviewText:
I've been drinking Gold Blend since I was a student in the 1970s, and assumed you'd just changed the packaging so filled my cupboard with it as usual.  But it's dreadful.  As others have said, if you want grit at the end of your drink you can make real coffee.  Instant is meant to be a convenient and gorgeous tasting/feeling drink. I don't like tea so drink coffee all the time - and DON'T want to hate it.
If you wanted to change it so completely, why not bring out a new blend featuring "non-dissolving, grit at the end" so at least customers have a choice?
As it is, I'm going to have to change my brand after all this time.  I have a jar of a different product, and I'm looking forward to all the Gold Blend being used up so that I can try it.
But I'd much rather you brought Gold Blend back.

After telling family and friends for 40+ years that nothing is as good as Gold Blend, I would no longer recommend it - now telling family and friends that you've ruined it.
Results.Title: What have you done?

Results.ReviewText:
I probably drink more coffee than i should, so after tasting every brand and that includes supermarket own brands, I always come back to the master, Gold Blend.

No other instant  has that rich,smooth and slightly bitter taste that only the best coffee can give you. It is consistent in every jar and gives fantastic value for money.
Results.Title: The one and only

Results.ReviewText: We married 32 years ago and have always drunk Nescafe coffee, starting with Nescafe original but switched to Gold Blend. A change we have never regretted. It would be difficult to find such a pleasant tasting and overall enjoyable cup of coffee as Gold Blend. It is neither bitter nor too strong but is a smooth and comfortable drink.
Results.Title: Fabulous beverage

Results.ReviewText: Simply the best instant coffee on the market in my humble opinion. I don't feel I can really start the day until I've enjoyed a cup of Gold Blend Original. Lovely rich and welcoming aroma combined with a bitter sweet taste really helps give me the lift I need. I honestly don't know what I'd do without this product. Coffee heaven!
Results.Title: My daily coffee!
